= Section 1: Quantitative Reasoning

*Approximate Time:* 15 minutes | *Questions:* 6-7

== Introduction

Quantitative Reasoning tests mathematical problem-solving skills. All questions are Problem Solving (PS) format with 5 answer choices.

== Topics Covered

#uptoten-table(
  columns: 3,
  header: ("Topic", "Sample Questions", "What to Expect"),
  "Number Properties & Arithmetic", "1", "Integers, primes, divisibility",
  "Algebra", "1-2", "Equations, inequalities, functions",
  "Word Problems", "1", "Rate, work, distance problems",
  "Statistics & Probability", "1", "Mean, median, probability",
  "Percents, Ratios & Proportions", "1-2", "Percentage changes, ratios",
)

== Sample Question Format

#info-box[
  *Example Question Structure:*

  A store offers a 20% discount on an item originally priced at \$80. If sales tax of 8% is applied after the discount, what is the final price?

  (A) \$64.00
  (B) \$69.12
  (C) \$70.40
  (D) \$72.00
  (E) \$86.40

  *What to notice:*
  - One question stem
  - Five answer choices (A-E)
  - Only one correct answer
  - Often includes calculations with specific numbers
]

